.TH "CITADEL" "1" "Jul 2026" "AceTeam" "Citadel CLI Manual"

.SH NAME
citadel-module-update - Re-resolve installed modules and re-install any that changed


.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBcitadel module update [] [flags]\fP


.SH DESCRIPTION
Re-resolve each installed module's source from the lockfile and re-install
any whose resolved commit changed (constraint/channel refs re-resolve against the
latest tags). Prints what changed.

.PP
If a re-installed module declares a health_check and is currently running, it is
restarted and probed; on a definitively-unhealthy result the previous version is
restored (best-effort rollback).


.SH OPTIONS
\fB-h\fP, \fB--help\fP[=false]
	help for update

.PP
\fB--prune\fP[=false]
	After updating, garbage-collect cache dirs no longer referenced by the lockfile.

.PP
\fB--restart\fP[=true]
	Restart a changed module's container if it is currently running (needed for the health-rollback probe).


.SH OPTIONS INHERITED FROM PARENT COMMANDS
\fB--debug\fP[=false]
	Enable debug output

.PP
\fB--no-auto-update\fP[=false]
	Disable automatic update checks and installs for this run (or set CITADEL_NO_AUTO_UPDATE=1)

.PP
\fB--no-color\fP[=false]
	Disable colorized output


.SH SEE ALSO
\fBcitadel-module(1)\fP
